<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,774,1844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,421,890,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Description. Tube</emphasis>
: Ten 
<bibRefCitation author="Hove" box="[490,700,890,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" refString="Hove, H. A. ten. (1973) Serpulinae (Polychaeta) from the Caribbean: II - The Genus Sclerostyla. Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands, 43, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1973">
Hove (
<number box="[570,634,890,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1973.0">1973</number>
: 
<number box="[646,691,890,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
describes it as variable with regard to colour and longitudinal ridges. It is white to pinkish in colour, with usually three but may be four or more longitudinal ridges, all variations occurring in the same locality or even on the same tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,774,1844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,276,1006,1032]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Worm</emphasis>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[297,329,1007,1033]" name="American Samoa" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">As</collectingCountry>
seen in the above material from 
<collectingCountry box="[741,837,1007,1033]" name="Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Bonaire</collectingCountry>
, operculum calcareous, inserted independently of branchial radioles of both sides (
<figureCitation box="[540,612,1045,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,258,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[299,1293,654,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[273,1314,629,1941]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal view of anterior end of Pyrgopolon ctenactis (Mørch, 1863) from Station 212, Santa Barbara, Bonaire, collected, determined and presented by ten Hove, BM (NH) 1971: 230. Note operculum inserted independently of branchial radioles of both sides, i. e., from the middle of the anterior end of the thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186803/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number box="[596,612,1045,1071]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); funnel-shaped, smooth on the outside, scalloped along the rim, and with a toothed ridge corresponding to each scallop extending along the inside of the funnel (see also ten 
<bibRefCitation author="Hove" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" refString="Hove, H. A. ten. (1973) Serpulinae (Polychaeta) from the Caribbean: II - The Genus Sclerostyla. Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands, 43, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1973">
Hove, 
<number box="[151,212,1122,1148]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 
<number box="[276,395,1122,1148]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="27.15" valueMax="29.3" valueMin="25.0">25–29, 30</number>
– 
<number box="[411,440,1122,1148]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="33.0">33</number>
, plates 
<number box="[529,577,1122,1148]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
). Peduncle: solid, calcareous, continuous with the calcareous operculum; wingless. Interradiolar membranes present; thoracic membranes extend to end of thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1264,1340,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,258,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[299,1293,654,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[273,1314,629,1941]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal view of anterior end of Pyrgopolon ctenactis (Mørch, 1863) from Station 212, Santa Barbara, Bonaire, collected, determined and presented by ten Hove, BM (NH) 1971: 230. Note operculum inserted independently of branchial radioles of both sides, i. e., from the middle of the anterior end of the thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186803/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number box="[1323,1340,1161,1187]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); apron present (not shown in figure 
<number box="[488,504,1200,1226]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,774,1844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,301,1238,1264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Chaetae</emphasis>
: Collar chaetae may be absent; when present, special collar chaetae may possess a distally papillate shaft, and a papillate boss (
<emphasis box="[575,612,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">see</emphasis>
ten 
<bibRefCitation author="Hove" box="[661,802,1277,1303]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" refString="Hove, H. A. ten. (1973) Serpulinae (Polychaeta) from the Caribbean: II - The Genus Sclerostyla. Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands, 43, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1973">
Hove, 
<number box="[739,802,1277,1303]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[812,829,1277,1303]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
, figs. 
<number box="[899,948,1277,1303]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1084,1278,1303]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1084,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-chaetae: absent. Uncini: sawshaped, most anterior uncinal process simple. Abdominal neurochaetae: geniculate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,774,1844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,1354,1380]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Remarks</emphasis>
: The description of genus 
<taxonomicName box="[638,775,1355,1380]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[638,775,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Pyrgopolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally based on the tube and operculum of its fossil 
<typeStatus box="[221,272,1393,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName box="[371,591,1393,1418]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mosae">
<emphasis box="[371,591,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Pyrgopolon mosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de 
<bibRefCitation author="Montfort" box="[633,812,1393,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="56" refString="Montfort, D. de (1808) Conchylogie systematique et classification methodique des coquilles, 1. Coquilles univalves, cloisonees. Paris, (F. Schoell), 1 - 409." type="journal article" year="1808">
Montfort, 
<number box="[753,812,1393,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1808.0">1808</number>
</bibRefCitation>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jager" box="[874,1004,1393,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="56" refString="Jager, M. (1993) Danian Serpulidae and Spirorbidae from NE Belgium and SE Netherlands: K / T boundary extinction, survival, and origination patterns, Contributions in Tertiary and Quarternary Geology, 29, 73 - 137." type="journal article" year="1993">
Jäger 
<number box="[943,1004,1393,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, p. 
<number box="[1045,1078,1393,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="95.0">95</number>
). However, as shown below, it is now possible to include characters of the worm itself, based on the 
<typeStatus box="[1035,1089,1432,1458]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
species of the extant genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,290,1471,1496]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Sclerostyla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,290,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Sclerostyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has been synonymized with 
<taxonomicName box="[739,885,1471,1496]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pyrgopolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[739,885,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Pyrgopolon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely, 
<taxonomicName authority="Morch, 1863" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[1008,1437,1471,1497]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Sclerostyla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ctenactis">
<emphasis box="[1008,1267,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Sclerostyla ctenactis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morch" box="[1276,1437,1471,1497]" pageId="6" pageNumber="56" refString="Morch, O. A. L., (1863) Revisio Critica Serpulidarum, et bidrag til rorormenes naturhistorie Naturhistorisk Tiddskrift, Henrik Kroyer, Kobenhavn 8, 71 - 113." type="journal article" year="1863">
Mørch, 
<number box="[1375,1437,1471,1497]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1863.0">1863</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="Morch, 1863" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[178,721,1509,1535]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Serpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ctenactis" subGenus="Sclerostyla">
<emphasis box="[178,272,1510,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Serpula</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[291,425,1510,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Sclerostyla</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[443,551,1510,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">ctenactis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morch" box="[560,721,1509,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="56" refString="Morch, O. A. L., (1863) Revisio Critica Serpulidarum, et bidrag til rorormenes naturhistorie Naturhistorisk Tiddskrift, Henrik Kroyer, Kobenhavn 8, 71 - 113." type="journal article" year="1863">
Mørch, 
<number box="[656,721,1509,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1863.0">1863</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). A similar situation was encountered recently with regard another fossil serpulid genus, namely, 
<taxonomicName authority="Regenhardt, 1961" authorityName="Regenhardt" authorityYear="1961" box="[597,965,1548,1574]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Spiraserpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[597,749,1548,1573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Spiraserpula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Regenhardt" box="[755,965,1548,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="56" refString="Regenhardt, H. (1961) Serpulidae (Polychaeta: sedentaria) aus der Kreide Mitteleuropas, ihre Okologische, taxionomische und stratigraphische Bewertung. Mitteilungen aus dem Geologischen Staatsinstitut, Hamburg, 30, 5 - 115." type="journal article" year="1961">
Regenhardt, 
<number box="[904,965,1548,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was described on the basis of the tube of its fossil 
<typeStatus box="[345,396,1586,1612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Regenhardt, 1961" authorityName="Regenhardt" authorityYear="1961" box="[501,897,1586,1612]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Spiraserpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="spiraserpula">
<emphasis box="[501,679,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">S. spiraserpula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Regenhardt" box="[685,897,1586,1612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="56" refString="Regenhardt, H. (1961) Serpulidae (Polychaeta: sedentaria) aus der Kreide Mitteleuropas, ihre Okologische, taxionomische und stratigraphische Bewertung. Mitteilungen aus dem Geologischen Staatsinstitut, Hamburg, 30, 5 - 115." type="journal article" year="1961">
Regenhardt, 
<number box="[835,897,1586,1612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, on the basis of 
<number box="[1205,1234,1586,1612]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="19.0">19</number>
extant species of 
